reviews.text: Went in to checkout new menu.  Staff was impatient because  I had too many questions and could not make up my mind. Only three customers in store at the time (11:30am). I left without making a purchase.  IF I decide to go back I will  definitely  checkout menu online before returning
It's a nice place to eat at, The spacing is small, however, the customer service is very good,  nice and friendly.

It's too hot in there I can't believe whoever owns this would let there business get that hot. You know the food isn't being kept cold..... subway really needs to get it together. Avoid subway go to nearby restaurants!
Seems very cramped inside. Not as busy or as well kept as it used to be. But, my sandwich was good, and the young lady was very polite.
Why did they charge me for a plastic bag?

𝗧𝗮𝘀𝘁𝘆 𝗙𝗼𝗼𝗱 & 𝗦𝘁𝗿𝗼𝗻𝗴 𝗗𝗿𝗶𝗻𝗸𝘀. My visit to San Antonio's Bar & Grill was amazing. The service was fast and people friendly. This is definitely a great atmosphere for girls night or even Mommy and Daughter dates, which was the reason for this visit. 𝗜 𝘄𝗼𝘂𝗹𝗱 𝗱𝗲𝗳𝗶𝗻𝗶𝘁𝗲𝗹𝘆 𝗿𝗲𝗰𝗼𝗺𝗺𝗲𝗻𝗱, 𝗛𝗮𝗽𝗽𝘆 𝗛𝗼𝘂𝗿! 𝗬𝗼𝘂 𝗰𝗮𝗻𝗻𝗼𝘁 𝗯ea𝘁 𝗱𝗮 𝗗𝗘𝗔𝗟𝗦!!!! Why I am able to #ᑕᕼOOᔕEᕼᗩᑭᑭY !!!

I absolutely love this place. I started out with the Gambas & Chile Con Queso. I forgot to take a picture because I was too busy socializing and sipping on my Jumbo Mango Margarita.  I must say this place is very inexpensive and the atmosphere is always great. My favorite location is in Crystal City because the chips are always fresh. However, the Lobster Fajita seen in the picture was Awesome and it comes out on a sizzling hot skillet. I loved this and I ordered a side of grilled veggies on the side squash, zucchini bell peppers and carrots. Highly recommend 10/10. The bartenders are great at all 3 locations.

Now I have been eating here for a while I pick up food here sometimes and I have never ever had any issues but today I ordered first thing in the morning on door dash two trays of fish tacos a chicken fajita meal and apple in a basket (dessert) which came up to $80 and I found a baby roach at the bottom of my desert which was covered in apples (by the way) and made me sick to my stomach knowing the fact that this came from the kitchen means it is unsanitary and more then likely more roaches running around. So disappointed! Do better

Definitely in love with the Happy Hour. Large Margaritas with multiple flavors. The food all around is good… hefty wings, tasty burgers, crunchy fresh chips, great FRIES, ETC. They have seating for large parties and outdoors. Perfect for a date night or just casual lunch with friends.

Cute Happy hour menu. This place has nicely priced Mexican cuisine and margaritas. It has some American cuisine as well but over all the food is good. The atmosphere is decent you see a mixed crowd here.

This little Neapolitan pizza place is amazing! I went for on a busy Saturday for lunch. There was only one staff but the waiter was so efficient and friendly. Pizzas were so delicious and the portions were big enough for me to bring half home. The Cappuccino Truffle is like an ice cream with coffee truffle in the center of the ice cream ball. It was pretty unique and tasty!

Brought my whole family here, two daughters,  2 son-in-laws, 3 grand kids. Very close to the taste of pizzas in Naples, Italy. Fast service and excellent taste. Antipasto tray good to. The serve Menabrea beer from Italy oldest brewery in Northern Italy. Looks to be dog friendly as well.

I had been hearing good things about this pizza and knew I had to give it a try. Every aspect was delicious: the sauce, the cheese, and the crust. From my experience in Italy, I think it is some of the most authentic Italian pizza that I have had in this area. My one thing for next time is that I will ask for them to spread more sauce and cheese on or get some extra sauce for dipping the crust. There was a lot more plain crust than I prefer, but it should be an easy thing to get around when I go back.

Great place for pizza in Washington DC !For a family of six the bill came to 90 dollars! We ordered a Caprese salad and a Formaggi Della casa plus three pizzas! Food is excellent and we enjoyed the dinner!
Tip: they closed at nine pm and hence do go early to enjoy your meal at leisure

Authentic Napoletana pizza. Warm and friendly neighborhood atmosphere with excellent service. This is the new favorite spot for my husband and I. I wish I could keep it a secret, but the food is so good and you can tell the staff works really hard and takes pride in what they serve. Really enjoyed my experience here and we will be back to try more pizzas.

This is by far the fastest Papa John's I  the DMV. I've ordered 3 times and I swear the pizza is so hot when it arrives that it burns my mouth.
It's difficult to find places in Northeast that consistently perform up to expectations. This Papa John's is definitely one of the places to go to
They brought me the wrong pizza, promised they'd be back in 10 minutes with the right order and never came back.

The pizza was soggy is hell, you can tell they stretch the pie to much. Wasn't cooked all the way thru was not how I ask. that was the 2nd time my order was wrong an that will be the last time I order from that location again.
Delicious and super fast delivery! Everything looks good! Pizza, wings, and the cinnamon pull aparts!
You all have one job..... My pizza is burnt. THIS IS RIDICULOUS
My pizza was delivered after 2 hours and 22 minutes that was promised between 36-46 minutes. It was cold. Instead of the garlic bread twists I ordered, I got cinnamon twists.

Philly cheesesteak pizza is still the best around. Atmosphere was clean and calm. Manager was very attentive of me. Excellent experience...(PLEASE DO NOT ever take the cheesesteak pizza off the menu ....EVER!!!0

So this isn't an indictment on the staff at all, but on the policy. I called to place an order for pickup at 10:20pm. I'm driving toward the location to pick up pizza and wings for me and my friend. An automated customer service line picked up. Long story short, the automation let's me place an order, confirms what I wanted, tells me the price, then places me on hold.

After placing me hold for 2 minutes, the automated voice says, 'sorry, something went wrong with your order' and hangs up. No other explanation. By this time, I'm close by, so I pulled up and went inside to place the order.

They tell me then that Domino's stops taking pick up orders at 10pm, so they won't take my order. Obviously the register is not closed out, because delivery doesn't stop until midnight. So I'm trying to figure out, why the door is open like I can come in and place an order and why did the automated phone line waste my time? So I said, 'what your telling me is, I can order for delivery while I stand here, but have to go home and wait for you to deliver it? They said yes. So I just walked out and drove to Pizza Bolis nearby.

Yes, I could have ordered it for delivery, sat in my car and just intercepted the pizza when the delivery man came out to deliver to my house. But I was over the experience by then.

This location has never once gotten my order items wrong, which is why I’m sad to write this. But, the treatment that I received from the cashier that was also answering phones the other night was unacceptable. Not only did he personally degrade me when it was his driver in the wrong, he used foul language multiple times toward me repeatedly. After telling the cashier that the delivery person went to a different address, the cashier threatened me and told me that next time I need to put the right address in or I would face consequences. As a business student at a local university, I understand that this type of behavior is not only unprofessional but business and reputation ending. This employee should no longer be representing this store in threatening customers.

I ordered pizza online over a hour ago and still have not left the store. Just cancel the order I don’t understand why you have people waiting for they food I could have came a picked it up by now. Never again will order from this place

So I order a EX large pizza and a can soda‼️ Online delivery 45 to 55 mins... long story short I calls and inquire about my order they say oh it’s outside your door, and been there for 10mins! Smh I didn’t get a call nor a knock on my door... so when I told the guy on the phone that he started to be disrespectful and hung up on me! Lastly my pizza didn’t have any sauce on it at all just bread, cheese & pepperoni. I called back to address that issue Nd more disrespect! I told them I was gonna give them a bad review & I hung up.... Why the guy calls back playing on my phone & yelling  in my ear! This was my second time ordering from them 1st time things went okay but tonight they was mad rude & disrespectful.

This is by far the worst pizza boli's in the area. I order two orders of fries, a steak and cheese & two drinks. I never got my drinks which were about $3 a piece and our fries were incredibly salty. So salty to the point my son started to get a headache and had to stop eating them.

I called back and was on hold for a second only to be told that it's nothing that they can do and If I ordered again, they'll ensure I get my drinks the next time.
So I have to spend more money for you all to maybe get my order right?

Terrible experience, terrible food, never should have ordered from here

This location has horrible customer service and took an hour and 15 mins over delivery time to say that they would send another driver with a fresh order. (Location is 19 mins away) After calling 3 separate times to inquire about the order status, I was told no one knows the owners name and cannot provide his name due to policy.
SN: If you’re hungry for pizza in the Brookland  area I would recommend you to find some place else.
The best pizza around brookland! I love it
This place is amazing!! I love pizza boils !!! They are my favorite pizza ever!! I always order the Extra large Extra cheese pizza 😁🍕 ... And the prizes are so good!! I am here now 😀

Well i been working there for 7 year's now been all the bad and the good but try us again please we have NEW OWNER AL IS HIS NAME AND I TAKE ORDERS NOW AND SAUCE THE WINGS PLEASE COME CHECK ME OUT ON FRIDAY'S @ SUNDAY'S!  THANKS AND OVER AND OUT!  (MY NAME IS TRINA IF U NEED ANY HELP!
I wish I could leave a review but i called 5 times starting at 1:40 am on Sunday but nobody answered the phone. It says you're open at 12
Even though the owner doesn't seem to care this place IS open and is now D.C. Wings.

My sister & I came into the Brookland location & was met with an energetic & warm greeting.  The team on hand shared their knowledge of the simple & visually appealing ingredients & helped us navigate our customizable orders. I’m glad we made this gastro pit-stop today.  We’ll surely  return to visit our new friends Marc & Malik & enjoy more great pizza.  Thanks fellas!

I ordered 4 pizzas and they hardly had any ingredients on them. I’ve had better from other franchises. They didn’t have a chicken option. Will not order from here again or I will personally go in person to order.

Ok, the pizza was good. Very tasty.  Now, the other things. Fountain drink @ $2.75 is very pricey when a pizza is over $11.  The ambiance is tired, fixtures (table and counters) are worn out, and need to be refresh or a whole scale remodeling.  The place does not invite dinning in. Maybe, that's intentional.
&pizza use to look and taste taste better… mint favorite or impressed any more.

This was a terrible experience and the people there is just disrespectful, stay away from here if you appreciate being treated like a human being.
Tables are not cleaned and there is not soap on the bathrooms.

name: Potbelly
vicinity: 655 Michigan Avenue Northeast Ste B-4 Ste B-4, Washington

reviews.text: I had a very poor experience today while receiving my food. The food was ok but the service was very poor. My sandwich was burnt not toasted. I had to repeat myself multiple times only to find out when I got to my car that she had given me the wrong type of bread. I think they should do much better with their customer service .
I used to go here but they don't take cash now so I don't. Corporations and businesses that do this need to understand they're going to lose business. I'm not using a credit card for fast food LOL
Potbelly rarely disappoints this was no exception although my sandwich had more mayo than I would normally enjoy. It was a good meal.

Not bad but not particularly impressive.  It reminded me of a Quick Check sandwich.  The ordering process was a bit confusing.  The food was decent.  If your looking for a quick bite for a reasonable price this might be your place.

I ordered a bowl of chili and a Italian sub they literally put a whole piece of cheese in my chili and one piece of meat on my sub. If you don't like your job find another one instead of making ppl waste their hard earned money

name: Chipotle Mexican Grill
vicinity: 625 Monroe Street Northeast Ste A8, Washington

reviews.text: Just left this place. We drove down from Baltimore and  needed a quick bite so why not Chipotles? Nobody came to the counter to help us. When I asked if they were still taking orders, the guy got really rude for no reason. So We left! My money is a privilege not a necessity.

I love Chipotle, but the service at this location has a lot to be desired. Most of the time my order is wrong if I place an order on the app and pick it up/door dash from this location. The line has been broken down recently too, so they only did catering. Thankfully the Chipotle company is decent and will add free entree coupons when orders are wrong. But still, it’s very frustrating.

Single handedly the worst chipotle I have ever ordered from. They should clean house and fire every single person that works here. If you order online good luck getting what you ordered and expect a bowl of mostly rice.

The food is actually pretty good, to be owned by McDonald's. I don't recommend going near closing time when all the promo dishes are gone,  and the workers want to go home. Customer service begins to sink.

Love Chipotle but absolutely hate this location. I went there for a burrito bowl. I asked for extra sour cream on my bowl and the manager Elisendo charged me $1.55 for the extra serving. Never have I been charged for extra sour cream. The service here is terrible and it feels scammy

Staff are chill and explain things thoroughly. It took about 10 minutes to make my bacon and cheese sandwiches, and the bacon is crispy/chewy (personally I enjoy!). Paid $8 including tax and tip, so if you have $10 and want something local/have the diner experience, go here!
(Parking-wise, it's difficult, so I recommend coming here via Metro)

No frills greasy spoon diner. This has been out go to when we want a cheap and quick breakfast. You can always tell how good a El Salvadoran restaurant is by seeing who is eating in there. This place has a constant stream of DC natives that come in everyday.

The food is always great! They have just about every breakfast combination possible.  Service is slow sometimes probably because of the volume of orders. They need new chairs because most of them are falling apart. Overall, it's a great breakfast spot.

Most weekday mornings our Government crew comes in for breakfast. DELICIOUS DELICIOUS DELICIOUS!!!  I CRAVE AND DREAM the night before so i can eat BROOKLAND GRILL's Pecan Waffles!!! The burgers are thick,  meaty, & juicy!!! I AM IN LOVE!!! BROOKLYN GRILL is N.E.'s Little secret!!!  Thank you, B.G.
They have one of the best breakfast sandwiches I've ever had! They have a variety of options and the service is always quick and friendly! I visit whenever I get a chance! Stay safe!! ✌🏿

Decent place for wings. I would've liked the chicken wings to be a bit more spicy but good nonetheless. Mozzarella sticks with the sauce was fine and enjoyable. Garlic bread sucked though. It's next to my wings in the pictures. It wasn't fresh and didn't have taste whatsoever.
I ordered moon dust wings, all I could taste was the raw shrimp they had either on top or bottom of the chicken, chicken should taste like chicken, not fishy seafood!

Awesome hot wings!  I ordered 60 wings for the Super Bowl (30 Buffalo Hot and 30 Hot Lemon Pepper).  Big, tasty wings.  Seasoning was on point for both flavors.  All of my friends raved about how great the wings were.  Definitely go here for any catering or personal hot wing fixes!

Ok lets gooo! I'm beginning to think that America's Best Wings went out business and sold there storefronts to people that appear to be cooking the same thing. The price of chicken is very expensive and my issue is that when you ask for well done they fry the chicken to a point where it is not edible. On top of that I ordered the lemon pepper wings and they were covered in so much seasoning I couldn't eat any of them. Like no exaggeration they were a health hazard they had so much sodium on them. I have not been to this location in some time but would recommend if you go to look and taste your food prior to leaving.

Absolutely disgusting. I ordered a Caesar wrap and cheese fries. They put a poorly fried slab of a chicken tender in a doughy wrap with dressing I’ve never tasted before. The top layer of fries have a thin shell hard coating of what I assume is supposed to be cheese. UberEats ratings are so bad they wouldn’t even let me add to it so I came here. And I’m not a picky person at all. They need to be shut down until they can care enough about what they put on people’s plate. $30 down the drain. Inexcusable. Please eat somewhere else.
It was good just waited a long time for the food and did not receive a complimentary drink for waiting so long.
Employees behind the counter are not customer oriented, they are more interested in what they did over the weekend or the night before than taking your order and get it right.

Like every Chick-fil-A I've been to, the staff was friendly and the food was great. But the thing that impressed me most was the chalkboard on the wall at the counter, that had a different Bible verse written on it each day. Nice show of faith in the public square.

This is a college dining hall Chick-fil-a! The hours are not accurate and you must park, get out and walk in. Just a disclaimer before you head to this location. I love chick-fil-a, and am sure the food is good but the location is not properly advertised.
Great hospitality great tasting food great service if you haven't been to chick-fil-a you are missing out buddy 😤👌🏾

name: Murphy's Grill
vicinity: Edward J. Pryzbyla University Center, 620, Michigan Avenue Northeast, Washington

reviews.text:
This food is 🔥. You won't be hungry eating here! Great menu with lots of options of food.
No bar service still and it's only open for lunch, but delicious!
Highly recommend the fish and chips and crab dip appetizers is a must!

Great restaurant to be hidden inside a campus but well worth the visit. Friendly and accommodating staff. Simple but tasty food. Small but good variety on the menu including the mix on the alcohol. Also can do private functions and happy hour gatherings. Great specials and make sense for the season or holidays. Best prices in the area.

The place has great potential. It's cosy and well designed with great service. But the burger meat was from one of those cheap frozen packs you get in Giant or Target - the meat was soggy from the freezer and tasted like tissue paper covered with herbs. The steak fries were great though. If they invest in better quality meat I'd be back.

This is a great bar and restaurant. Everyone at CUA should and largely does eat here. Ingrid is a great manager and the staff are all very good! The food is good and the drinks are very enjoyable. The seating arrangements is accomodating for large or small groups.

First burger over cooked. Should have been med rare, fries also cold. I send it back the next burger came out in 2 minutes. Now under cooked fries still cold. Not good. A burger is the easiest thing to cook. As a chef for over 20 years I would have fired the person on the grill on the spot.
Tasty chicken wings, plus nice service! I would love to support this mom-and-pop shop around the corner.

Prices are too high! I understood why it was soo high last year & in the beginning of the year but things around the world are back open & supply &’demand isn’t as high as before. So drop the prices back to what it used to be or at least offer coupons like before. We trying soo hard to keep you guys in business but you’re robbing us at this point. 3 wings & fries shouldn’t be $15.00

I’ve been eating here since I was 8 years old, I’m 26 now. & for the last 2 years prices have shy rocket. & they don’t even offer free things if u order over uh certain amount! It’s sad & not fair how they over charging us! I hate it! 4 wings with fries shouldn’t be $16! You guys are gonna lose him customers, if u can’t satisfy customers why not just close down for good

This restaraunt could be better the food is hit or miss not always consistent. They are very stubborn about correcting their mistakes. Instead they blame you and give you a hard way to go no matter how respectful you are when conveying the mistake they made. Use to be our favorite family carryout but not anymore.

I stopped by earlier & when I heard them prices i left out & went around the corner to Jerry’s Carryout. Sammy’s keeps upping prices & I can’t afford it anymore. I tried to order uh half of steak & cheese wit fries & ended up having to pay over $13! But at other Carryout’s it’s only $9.00 .
Do better Sammy’s you guys lost uh customer & I’ve been coming for 9 years

Tried their chicken boneless kabob platter. Kabobs we’re well cooked, so juicy. Absolutely loved the taste and texture of kabob. Chicke pea curry could’ve  been better. Would definitely go back to try their buffet

I have been to countless South Asian restaurants and spent a lot of money. But today, I found my ultimate guilty pleasure of mine.

Buffet for 15 dollars with 8 Authentic Asian dishes, this is what you live for. Being a south asian far from home, I m finally feeling like I found a home.

Will come back again and again. Must try!

Expected sub par...you know just a little dine in dine out spot. PLEASANTLY surprised...even with how they serve the food in the traditional pot! I was eat humming in my head. Glad I did not request xtra spicy, don't think I would have been able to handle. Never had lamb biryani  but chicken and I am hooooked. It was very delicious. I wanted to try the mango lassi but I am off sugar right now. I forgot to get me the samosa. Because I am in Ft Washington for the weekend I ordered Lamb curry for my next night dinner. I do want to try their lamb shanks so might have to take a drive Friday when they will have.
Wish they were in my city, I thoroughly enjoyed and the owner was very nice and welcoming.
I did hear him mention outside dining, so that probably happens in warmer weather. If I visit again at that time, would like to experience.
P.s. from the way I was coming google maps said turn left. It was on the right. I made many circles before I realized. So glad I kept looking 🤣

One my absolute all time favorite restaurants in DC, and I don't say that lightly. It's so good that if I lived in walking distance, I would never leave. Food is always impeccable and delicious. I wish my cooking was even half as good. Generous portions and excellent prices for what get. Staff is always kind, efficient, and welcoming.
This place is so clean, and good.

You go to some restaurants in DC and you really wonder how much the staff and ownership cares. You see dirty restaurants, small portions, and unwelcoming service. But not here. City Kabob could teach a masterclass on being in the service industry.

See all these other great reviews? They earned them. DC is lucky to host this incredible restaurant!

Amazing food,amazing people.We let them know that we were there for iftar, and they shared their fruit custard ( complimentary) with us as our ordered food wasn't ready by that time.Food was delicious. We will be visiting this place. Their samosa is very big and chicken tikka was finger licking good.

Unique neighborhood tea shop with so much more to offer.  I had a delicious Matcha Maca and a Spinach pastry (so good, just the right amount of heat).  Loved the variety of bagged teas and accessories.  Can’t wait to try more.  Nice seating area outside.

Calabash is the best! When you come to Calabash, the team will ask you how you’re feeling to help direct you to a healing drink. They also have TONS of goodies to purchase for use at home, too.

Their outdoor patio is a perfect way to spend an afternoon.

Great reprieve from the hustle and bustle. Wonderful place for small kids AND fur babies- hard feat in a small space. Delicious, affordable, healthy and staff is beyond helpful and efficient.  Great experience!!!!

At Calabash Tea & Tonic each customer is given a warm reception.  Recommendations for both food and beverage are expertly offered upon request based upon what you seek.  Many customers purchased products for personal use as well as as gifts during my late December 2022 visit.  This warm and inviting spot is a favored gathering location for locals to sip, chill, eat and relax and accommodates group gatherings as well.

What a vibe! I was not prepared for how much I'd like this spot. Came in for a tea to go (person behind the counter was SUPER helpful, btw), left with a bag of tea for the fall season and some soap. Can't wait to come back and try more. In the meantime, I'm going to shop the online store!

This is a great soul food restaurant. There are so many meat choices and sides. Everyone in the family can find something they like. The food is set up somewhat like a buffet but the staff prepares all of the plates. You stand and line and can see the food as it’s being prepared for your to go box. The food is always fresh and the portions are large. We always have left overs. The quality of the food is excellent. We always have great experiences when we eat here. The fried fish and beef ribs are a must try. The Mac and cheese is excellent. The cakes are moist and flavorful too. You’ll be sure to love it.

A friend that lives in MARYLAND recommended this place to us while visiting. It did not disappoint us. The service was great. The food was Awesomely Good. The restaurant was clean and the servers wore plastic gloves as they served us our very huge portions of food. It was also my husband bday and they sang him a happy birthday song. Everything about our first visit here was on point. We will definitely be back again.

GHETTO but the food is GREAT

There was a wait because they were busy and seemingly understaffed. The waiting area is right by the kitchen… ❗️BAD DECISION❗️

I hear one waitress talk about how she wants to (blank) somebody up & she doesn’t have time for the (redacted).

Another waitress spills a cup of sweet tea coming out of the kitchen and most of the staff walk right by it. One waiter who noticed decided to pick up and move all the ice out of the way of traffic. I referred to him as the super waiter. I wish we had him. Short light skinned and loud. He needs to train the rest of the staff. He was engaging with his tables and very warm.

A pregnant woman gets there and possibly got bad take out service and literally tried to start a fight and broke a vase. It took them 15mins to get the Asian lady to clean that up. some of the glass broke in the area of a new born. I guess the aforementioned lady does all the cleaning since she was the same one who cleaned the sweet tea from earlier and now the vase and latter cleaned off our table.

We had a rather sizable party, our waiter starts by letting us know that the bill can ONLY be split 3 ways. Also never gave us the first time welcome other tables got.

🥗🥓 The Food
That cornbread with cinnamon based and butter. Addictive. Mac & Cheese is okay for franchise mac & cheese. Yams were on the money. Crab meat was fresh salmon was perfect shrimp were nice and everything was seasoned to perfection. My plate was called the Carolina Salmon. Sweet Tea is southern and the hostess was very nice.
Once the food came out not one complain and not one unhappy person with their meal. Even a few to go containers. Peach cobbler was 3 out of 5. (It was given to me to go as asked but I think it was semi frozen)

This place is unbelievable, first walk in, the guys name “Charles “ was so nice ! He provided  the best service! ! I never see a man cool like him ! It is our first time be in the restaurant, and I think they get the traditional way to welcome to first time customers. Just prepare for that😂😂
This place is awesome! Food is delicious 😋! Definitely will go to the restaurant again!

This place has some excellent food… if it’s your first time in the establishment, the rejoicing that they give to you makes you feel extremely welcomed☺️.  The biscuits was absolute 🔥 the Mac and cheese was excellent!  It was my first time there but I will definitely have to make a return trip next time im back in the DC area!  Here’s a pic of one of the many plates our table had.  I’d share the other plates but… they were too busy eating and photo of their plates were the last thing they were thinking about 😄. The waiter even made you feel like he was a part of your family… loved the whole vibe!

Great food. I've had the wings, cheesy bacon fries, salad. The customer service is subpar. The workers aren't necessarily rude but there aren't enough. Typically they have the same person cooking and taking orders which causes a delay in ordering and getting anything that you may need from behind the counter (like ranch or ketchup if its not out). Still great food, just know you may have to be patient.

Really cool place the ambiance is amazing I love the boxing theme and all the paintings on the wall.  So many small details in the design of this place that really impressed me.  Service was great!  Had the black bean burger and fries it was really good definitely recommend!

First time trying this place and will never ever eat here again. The cashier is excellent and have awesome customer service, the crispy chicken sandwich on the other hand has me sick as a dog right now. It doesn't say anything about bacon on this sandwich instead it had a raw piece of bacon on it. Well that raw bacon(even though I didn't eat it) has given me food poisoning. I will never eat here again. Thank you but no thank you.

Went here last for dinner ,horrible experience.  My food for 2 persons took approx. An little less the an hour abt 45minuntes. When I got my order it was wrong . Wrong burger, wrong sides. They even ran out of cheddar cheese. Servers where nice and apologetic. But the organization of the restaurant was horrible.  More like a unmanaged moms and pop greasy spoon than an well rounded experience I expected. Disappointed at the experience. Will I visit again? Maybe alone, but as for another casual dinner date night. TOO Burger embarrassed me.

Food was really good the first two times I ate there. But I went there April 1st on a Sunday and my food still wasn't coming to me after 50 minutes. So I made a phone call to try to pass time and you can see employees walking back and forth laughing and staring at me like I'm the one with the problem I seriously just want my food is all so I asked for a refund and 1 other customer asked for one as well which then a lady walked to the register took the ladies receipt gave her cash because she paid with cash and I paid with credit she took my receipt and just threw it away and said have a nice day so I believed she was gonna do something in the system to refund me. it's been over a week and I'm now out of 24 dollars for no food and a horrible experience if you don't like your job choose one your happy at and gimme my money when you ever get the chance. Last note why have a business phone number you never pick up? It's in google

I can't say enough good things about this place. The beer is the best in town, the owners are amazing, the staff are incredibly friendly, and the music venue upstairs is great. If you get a chance to stop in for a beverage and a show, you won't be disappointed.  D.C. isn't exactly a hotbed for good beer despite the number of breweries, but this place is an exception. Although limited in quantity, they certainly exceed others in quality. They have food available some nights from a pop-up kitchen in the back, and the space upstairs is very inviting and laid back.

I came here for an event. Even though I was early the two owners upfront were very hospitable. Got me drinks very quickly. They did not have their own food there but had @chefces on Instagram serving her food there. It was amazing. Atmosphere for the event was great as well. First open nice of the year. Great place. They do tours as well.
Went to see Lorenzo & Co with Smoking on planes & Oh Violet had a great time. Great drinks, good music and great folks all ages just having a good time. Love the atmosphere, will definitely be back!
Went there for an event last Saturday. Decided to try beers and have a bite to eat before the show. Everything we ordered was delicious.Very nice low key place, pleasant atmosphere . Thank you.

Last night was my first night living in the neighborhood, and I happened to walk by and walk into this place. I'm so grateful that I did. This is the kind of place that makes me hesitate to give it the great rating it deserves, because I'm afraid of it getting too busy and changing. But man, does it deserve it.

You cannot find new places this genuine. Bill (the brewer and DC born-and-raised) and his wife Kathy run an amazing little place that is as genuine as it gets, with spectacular beer (loved the Cream Ale best of what I had, but the Porter and the Rye IPA were both delicious as well), locally-distilled liquor and delicious veggie dogs (I tried the jerk plantain and the spicy eggplant/mushroom and I want more, but there's a Buffalo cauliflower still to try). Upstairs there was exceptional live music, but I didn't have the time to commit to it.

It's only open Fridays and Saturdays, but it's so worth it if you like value, excellence and authenticity. It's even better if you're in the neighborhood, because the clientele is mostly local and very friendly.
